and evaporated in quick succession. Drawing from environmental history, US history and the history of science, and extensively mining a wealth of antebellum agricultural publications, The Nature of the Future uncovers the rich loam hiding beneath ostensibly infertile scholarly terrain, revealing a surprising area of agricultural experimentation that transformed American landscapes and American ideas of expertise, success, and exploitation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aAgriculturexCapital productivityzNew York (State)xHistoryy19th century. 0aAgriculturexCapital productivityzNew York (State)xHistoryy19thcentury. 0aAgriculturezNew York (State)xHistoryy19th century. 0aCrop sciencezNew York (State)xHistoryy19th century. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh  aMarket Revolution.  aUnited States history.  aagricultural improvement.  aagricultural science.  aenvironmental history.  ahistory of capitalism.  ahistory of science.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020 Englishz978311070473008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020z9783110704525oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z97831106930960 cprintz978022669383540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226693972423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226693972/original  a978-3-11-069309-6  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070473-0  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2020 English